\b Usage\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf2 \
Example song uses pattern length 128, LPB 8. You have a hi hat on every two lines (16th notes). Now you move the cursor to pattern line 02, press option-y (flexible mark below line shortcut) to select everything starting with this line. You place your cursor to the delay column. You setup a edit step of 4. Multiple press the shortcut +1. Now you have a classic shuffle.\
