Affects all occurrences of the note under the cursor (and its octaves) either in the selection or in the track (if selection is disabled). You can transpose -1/+1, delete or set-to-off the occurrences.\
\
It's to transpose just one note in a sequence, but also every repetition of this note plus its octaves. Like searching and replacing a note, only much more simple to use.\
 \

\b Usage\
\pard\pardeftab560\slleading20\partightenfactor0

\b0 \cf2 \
You have a track with an arp note sequence. You changed the bass' note and now quickly want to fix one or more multiple occurring notes in the arp. Select the whole track, move cursor over the note that should be transposed and use shortcut.\
